

The signals sped across the emptiness,
6.8 parsecs to Sol and 9.4 in the other
direction.


Though the NASA and ESA scientists who
received it worked with utmost speed, it
still took five years to launch a manned
expedition to Gliese 667 to respond to
the signal, and over a hundred years for
that craft they built to make the voyage.


When the descendents of the original
crew finally entered orbit around the
third planet, the old probe which had
summoned them had rusted away long
since.


But by then the outpost had been rebuilt
and expanded by its original creators,
who eagerly welcomed those weary fellow
travelers.






